2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the performance analysis of self-interference cancellation methods in a wireless communication system, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper involves the analysis of a complex system (full-duplex MIMO) and the performance of different self-interference cancellation methods, which can be categorized under systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper does not directly deal with multimedia, but the use of MIMO technology in wireless communication systems can have implications for multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): The paper does not deal with social or ethical issues related to computing, so this category is less likely.
